    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-10-31T18:11:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-10-31T18:11:00-05:00" n="560"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/10–2952: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">United States Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-10-31T18:11:00-05:00"
                            >October 31, 1952—6:11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss> 32. Re <gloss target="#t_Delga1"
                        >Delga</gloss> 77,<note n="1" xml:id="d560fn1">Not printed, but see <ref
                            target="#d559fn2">footnote 2, <ref target="#d559">
                                <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                            </ref>
                        </ref>.</note> Indians in South Africa.</p>
                <p>Since preliminary draft Indian res patterned upon <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss> resolutions adopted 1949, 1950 and 1952, it is generally
                    satisfactory to <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>. However, we hope <gloss
                        target="#t_GADel1">GADel</gloss> may be able induce Indians drop para 8
                    which provides for automatic inclusion item on 8th <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss> agenda on ground this para serves no real purpose since India
                    can always submit item in time for inclusion agenda next <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss> if situation requires, and para 8 implies that <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> anticipates <gloss>GOC</gloss> will fail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
